            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>roasted</strong> <strong>garlic paste</strong> and <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong> with 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[130ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [150ml]</span><strong> boiled water</strong> to the pan and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Cook for a further 3-4 min or until the prawns are cooked through and the sauce has thickened slightly – this is your <strong>jumbo prawn saganaki</strong></p><p>Note: Please make sure you cook your prawns thoroughly (until piping hot!) as cooking equipment varies</p>",
